---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout
  title="About — Easy Chat Maker"
  description="Why Easy Chat Maker exists: a free, no-watermark chat mockup generator for creators, marketers and anyone who needs a realistic fictional conversation."
  heading="About Easy Chat Maker"
>
  <p>
    Easy Chat Maker started with a simple frustration: making a believable chat screenshot for a
    video, a meme or a product demo took far too long. Free tools slapped a watermark across the
    result, interrupted typing with ads, or only supported one or two apps. Design tools like
    Photoshop could do it — if you had an hour to spare and pixel-perfect patience.
  </p>
  <p>
    So we built the tool we wanted: <strong>type a conversation, watch it appear on a phone in
    the style of a real messaging app, and export it — free, with no watermark and no
    signup.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>What it does</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Nine platform styles</strong> — WhatsApp-style, Instagram DM, Messenger, Telegram,
      Slack, Discord, and AI assistants: ChatGPT, Claude and Gemini.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Inline editing</strong> — click any bubble and type. Names, avatars, timestamps and
      reactions are all editable right on the phone preview.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Real group chats</strong> — multiple people with their own names, colors and
      avatars.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Two export formats</strong> — a pixel-clean PNG image, or an animated clip where
      messages appear one by one with typing indicators.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Private by design</strong> — everything runs in your browser. Your conversations
      never touch our servers.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who it's for</h2>
  <p>
    Content creators making chat-story videos and memes. Marketers turning customer conversations
    into social proof and product demos. Teachers, writers and storytellers mocking up dialogue.
    And anyone who wants to make their group chat laugh.
  </p>

  <h2>Our one rule</h2>
  <p>
    Mockups made here are fictional and should stay that way. We're proud to power creativity,
    comedy and marketing — not deception. Please don't use exports to trick, impersonate or harm
    anyone. The full details live in our <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <p>
    Feedback, feature requests and bug reports make the tool better every week. Say hello on the
    <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
